<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-06-26T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-06-26T11:00:00-05:00" n="509" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">652.113 Auto/62: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain (<persName type="from">Bowers</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary
                                        of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-06-26T16:00:00+00:00">June
                                        26, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received June 26—2:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>37. Your telegram No. 24, June 22 [<hi rend="italic">12</hi>], 5 p.m.
                                I am unofficially informed that Spain has granted “benefits” of 32
                                percent on French automobiles by an unpublished agreement which
                                parties apparently wish to keep secret. I have written a note of
                                inquiry to the Foreign Minister and will protest as soon as I can
                                obtain official confirmation.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>